        {
          "type": "final",
          "verdict": "findings_remain",
          "findings": [
            {
              "message": "`run_in_dir` changes the process-wide current directory and only restores it after the closure returns normally. If the closure panics, Rust unwinds past the restore call, leaving later tests running from the temp repo directory (which may then be deleted), so tests using this shared helper are no longer independent. Restore via a guard/drop or `catch_unwind` so cleanup happens on both success and panic paths.",
              "severity": "P1",
              "file": "apps/cli/src/commands/track/mod.rs",
              "line": 643,
              "category": "test_isolation"
            }
