          "type": "fast",
          "verdict": "zero_findings",
          "findings": [],
          "hash": "rvw1:sha256:495d20e7b29d97b0010dbb7fe5327bd57e4d81c4f7fc20a6bb954466c438b51b",
          "at": "2026-06-05T09:04:58Z"
        },
        {
          "type": "final",
          "verdict": "findings_remain",
          "findings": [
            {
              "message": "T005 claims that after the non-git passthrough migration no Makefile.toml non-git route still calls `bin/sotp make`, and T004 relies on that before deleting the make subcommand. However spec IN-03 includes `track-baseline-capture` in the non-git passthrough set, while the plan leaves that wrapper removal to T009, which runs after T004. This makes the dependency order internally inconsistent: T004 can delete `bin/sotp make` while the `track-baseline-capture` cargo-make wrapper still exists and may still route through it.",
              "severity": "P1",
              "file": "track/items/cargo-make-teardown-2026-06-05/impl-plan.json",
              "line": 24,
              "category": "infeasibility"
            }
          ],
          "hash": "rvw1:sha256:495d20e7b29d97b0010dbb7fe5327bd57e4d81c4f7fc20a6bb954466c438b51b",
          "at": "2026-06-05T09:07:31Z"
        },
        {
          "type": "fast",
          "verdict": "findings_remain",
          "findings": [
            {
              "message": "`track-signals` has two different removal points in the plan: T005 already removes it from `Makefile.toml` (`plan.md:26`), but S6/S8 still describe it as a wrapper that survives until T009 (`plan.md:46`, `plan.md:60`). T009's actual task body only removes `track-baseline-capture` (`plan.md:63`), so the wrapper's lifecycle is internally contradictory.",
              "severity": "P1",
              "file": "/home/flip451/individual/t-rust/templates/SoTOHE-core/track/items/cargo-make-teardown-2026-06-05/plan.md",
              "line": 46,
              "category": "contradiction"
            }
          ],
          "hash": "rvw1:sha256:cd324f180e21ba11daa4d817b94a3f85ccfb28c2918f4c73486e69ae1822461c",
          "at": "2026-06-05T09:16:33Z"
        },
        {
          "type": "final",
          "verdict": "findings_remain",
          "findings": [
            {
              "message": "CN-03 requires any cargo make task that invokes `bin/sotp git <sub>` to use `command`/`args` arrays and explicitly not an `@shell` script, but AC-06 and T008 require `commit`/`track-commit-message` to be a 6-step `@shell` script that invokes `bin/sotp git add-all` and `bin/sotp git commit-from-file`. As written, the plan cannot satisfy both the constraint and the commit-script acceptance/task requirements; CN-03 needs an explicit D6 orchestration exception or the T008/AC-06 design needs to change.",
              "severity": "P1",
              "file": "track/items/cargo-make-teardown-2026-06-05/spec.json",
              "line": 274,
              "category": "contradiction"
            }
          ],
